The "deprecation" path we agreed on for this was to implement the correct thing and silently accept the current incorrect header for backward compatibility.  You'll need to make sure there's a test accepting the incorrect header to prevent regressions (put a comment or docstring on the test explaining the situation for the benefit of future glancers).

Patch Set 14: Code-Review-1

I just realized one more thing partial image downloads. With or without this change, partial image downloads work ONLY if the backend store supports random read access. Currently, only the filesystem and cinder stores support it. Other stores will return the entire image. This will result in another bug because if we find a Range/Content-Range header in the request, we return 206 in response with a Content-Range header, which is incorrect if we are returning the entire image.

So, I'm thinking we should verify whether the current store is capable of random reads. If it is, continue doing what we do here. If not, return the entire image with 200.
